Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharp turn. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 200, 21. Name Agesilas. Probably from same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum MGR 1115.17.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0752)
